I would recommend against using an &quot;o&quot; even for a private &quot;work-around&quot; 
when that is not the sound needed for the word.  In my opinion, you want 
to indelibly link the QS letters with the sounds they represent in your 
mind to foster automatic reading, i.e. without the necessity of sounding 
out words.  After all, this is what we do with T.O.

I think the use of a letter that represents a different sound in place 
of the correct letter, would be counter productive and harmful to your 
comprehension.  I would just advise you to realize that QS does not 
require that every letter be joined to every other letter.  QS is quite 
cursive as Read designed it.  The small amount of time required for the 
occasional pen-lift, is not worth the confusion of muddying the phonemic 
character, might I say, &quot;purity,&quot; of the alphabet.

Just my two cents.


Paige Gabhart


